# Mostro StartOS — Core Rules

Package wrapper for [MostroP2P/mostro](https://github.com/MostroP2P/mostro) on StartOS. SDK **1.5.3**, image `mostrop2p/mostro:v0.17.4`, required dep **LND**.

**Read `AGENTS.md` first** for full architecture, workflows, and debugging. Deeper guides: `development-docs/`, `start-docs/packaging/src/`.

## Use current paths only

Edit SDK 1.5 layout — **not** legacy `startos/manifest.ts`, `startos/file-models/`, or `startos/install/versions/`.

## Golden rules

1. Match existing patterns — read sibling files before adding code
2. Minimize scope — only change files required for the task
3. File models: **always `merge()`**, never `write()`
4. Every Zod schema key needs `.catch(default)`
5. Wrap user-visible strings in `i18n()`
6. Prefill actions with `.once()`, reactive reads with `.const(effects)`
7. Verify image tags, config keys, and SDK APIs — don't guess
8. Compiling ≠ working — state what was verified end-to-end
9. Update `instructions.md` for user-visible changes
10. Don't commit unless the user asks

## Adding a setting (checklist)

1. `startos/fileModels/settings.ts` — Zod field with `.catch()`
2. `startos/actions/<action>.ts` — `inputSpec`, prefill, save via `daemon_settings.merge`
3. `settings.tpl.toml` — key under correct `[section]`
4. New action? → register in `startos/actions/index.ts`
